'''Asif Kamal''' is an [[India]]n [[businessman]] based in [[Dubai]]. He is the founder chairman of [[Dubai]] based [[Alturaash Art and Culture.|Alturaash Art and Culture]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://artanddeal.in/cms/?p=3677|title=Art & Deal Magazine » COVER STORY|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Kamal|first1=Asif|title=Alturaash determined to upkeep the prestige of indian art and artists.|date=24 July 2016|publisher=eindiadiary.com|location=Mumbai|url=http://eindiadiary.com/alturaash-determined-to-upkeep-the-prestige-of-indian-art-and-artists-asif-kamal/|accessdate=24 July 2016}}</ref> He has been doing several notable work in the field of [[Indian Art]] <ref>{{cite news|title=More Fake Trouble for Indian Art.|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/More-fake-trouble-for-Indian-art-mart/articleshow/37361828.cms|accessdate=19 July 2016|agency=TNN|publisher=Times Of India.}}</ref> and started unique investment called ArtFund which provides loan against Indian modern and contemporary artwork with startup investment of 500 Crore Indian Rupees <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.firstpost.com/fwire/deposit-your-artwork-get-a-loan-1638755.html|title=Deposit your artwork, get a loan! - Firstpost|date=28 July 2014|publisher=}}</ref> It is the only Non- Banking Financial Corporation to provide loan against Indian Art.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.webnewswire.com/node/3606806|title=Now get instant loans against art with launch of first-ever Art Fund in India - webnewswire.com|publisher=|access-date=2016-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817041529/http://www.webnewswire.com/node/3606806|archive-date=2016-08-17|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>
==In the media==
In April 2016, he sent legal notice to Astaguru.com an online auction house in [[Mumbai]] to apologize to the public for putting up a fabricated fake art for auction, the claimed artwork was by the artist [[Manjit Bawa]]. Though no apology was forthcoming but the work was withdrawn from auction.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indialegalonline.com/the-great-indian-rip-off/|title=The Great Indian Rip-off|date=18 April 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Christies Rubbishes Claim by Dubai based art house.|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/christies-rubbishes-claim-by-dubai-based-art-house/1/547744.html|accessdate=18 June 2016|agency=India Today|issue=15 December 2015|publisher=India Today|date=15 December 2015}}</ref>
